## New Project: bellows
- **Replaces:** pako (~50M weekly npm downloads, 6.1k GitHub stars, 3,746 dependents, single npm maintainer vitaly, last release v2.1.0 Nov 2022 (3.5 years), 23 open issues, 4 unmerged PRs, issue #293 seeking maintainers, 100% JavaScript, no TypeScript, Tidelift-supported but unmaintained)
- **Why:** Unmaintained 3.5 years. No built-in TypeScript (4.1M weekly @types/pako downloads). fflate exists but has completely different API — NOT a drop-in replacement. No pako-compatible alternative exists.
- **Package:** @agentine/bellows (verified available on npm)
- **Features:** Native API delegation (Node.js zlib + browser CompressionStream), full pako API (deflate/inflate/gzip/ungzip/deflateRaw/inflateRaw), streaming Deflate/Inflate classes, all pako options (level, windowBits, memLevel, strategy, dictionary, raw, to, chunkSize), pako compat layer (bellows/compat/pako), TypeScript-first, zero dependencies, ESM+CJS dual package, Node.js 18+
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #879 (scaffolding), #880 (core types/constants), #881 (Node.js backend), #882 (browser backend), #883 (tests + release)

